20Ford%20Transit%2C%20after%20a%20recall%20had%20been%20issued%20for%20the%20vehicles%20in%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.nhtsa.gov%2Frecall-spotlight%2Fford-0%23%3A~%3Atext%3DSummary%26amp%3Btext%3DFord%2520Motor%2520Company%2520(Ford)%2520is%2Cthe%2520driveshaft%2520may%2520prematurely%2520fail.%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EJune%202017%20over%20safety%20issues.%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20concern%20was%20that%20%26quot%3Bthe%20flexible%20coupling%20between%20the%20transmission%20and%20driveshaft%26quot%3B%20of%20the%20vans%20could%20crack%20with%20extended%20use%2C%20causing%20the%20vehicles%20to%20potentially%20lose%20power%20on%20the%20road%20or%20start%20moving%20in%20park%20if%20the%20parking%20brake%20wasn't%20applied.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20NHTSA's%20consent%20order%20to%20Zipcar%20is%20the%20result%20of%20an%20investigation%20opened%20by%20the%20agency%20in%202018.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EOne%20of%20the%20agency's%20employees%20said%20they%20had%20rented%20a%20van%20from%20Zipcar%20in%20July%202017%2C%20only%20to%20discover%20the%20vehicle%20had%20an%20open%20recall%20that%20the%20car-sharing%20firm%20hadn't%20told%20them%20about%2C%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fstatic.nhtsa.gov%2Fodi%2Finv%2F2018%2FINIM-AQ18001-71738.pdf%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eper%20NHTSA%20records.%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20agency%20later%20concluded%20that%20Zipcar%20had%20rented%20out%20recalled%20Ford%20Transits%20up%20until%202018.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BVehicles%20with%20open%2C%20unrepaired%20recalls%20pose%20a%20safety%20risk%20to%20everyone%20on%20the%20road.%20NHTSA%20takes%20violations%20of%20the%20Safety%20Act%20very%20seriously%2C%26quot%3B%20Ann%20Carlson%2C%20the%20acting%20administrator%20for%20the%20NHTSA%2C%20said%20in%20the%20agency's%20statement.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIn%20addition%20to%20the%20fine%2C%20Zipcar%20has%20been%20instructed%20to%20send%20an%20audit%20report%20to%20the%20NHTSA%20on%20all%20Zipcar%20vehicles%20with%20open%20recalls%20within%20150%20days%20of%20the%20consent%20order.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20car-sharing%20firm%20will%20also%20have%20to%20revise%20its%20staff%20training%20on%20recalls%2C%20and%20have%20the%20updates%20assessed%20by%20third-party%20lawyers%20and%20sent%20to%20the%20NHTSA%20for%20review.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EA%20representative%20for%20Zipcar%20did%20not%20immediately%20respond%20to%20a%20request%20for%20comment%20sent%20outside%20regular%20business%20hours.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20company%20told%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fapnews.com%2Farticle%2Fzipcar-consent-order-car-recalls-nhsta-c648e4f10d53a362cd5e3a31dd022891%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EThe%20Associated%20Press%3C%2Fa%3E%20in%20a%20statement%20that%20fewer%20than%2050%20cars%20in%20its%20global%20fleet%20of%2012%2C000%20vehicles%20%26quot%3Bwere%20found%20in%20violation.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BAt%20Zipcar%2C%20we%20prioritize%20our%20members'%20safety%20and%20take%20manufacturers'%20recalls%20very%20seriously%2C%26quot%3B%20the%20company%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cdiv%3ERead%20the%20original%20article%20on%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fzipcar-fined-renting-recalled-ford-transits-nhtsa-2023-10%5C%22%3EBusiness%20Insider%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1697534255000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F652e50ea69c17ca46ae828a3%3Fformat%3Djpeg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fzipcar-fined-renting-recalled-ford-transits-nhtsa-2023-10%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22An%20NHTSA%20employee%20had%20rented%20a%20van%20from%20Zipcar%20in%202017%2C%20only%20to%20find%20out%20the%20vehicle%20had%20an%20open%20recall%20the%20company%20didn't%20tell%20them%20about%2C%20per%20NHTSA.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22mloh%40insider.com%20(Matthew%20Loh)%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A0%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fzipcar-fined-renting-recalled-ford-transits-nhtsa-2023-10%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22