g%20that%20Amazon%20hindered%20the%20vote.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAmazon%20disputed%20the%20Staten%20Island%20workers'%20unionization%20win%2C%20but%20its%20challenge%20failed%2C%20and%20the%20vote%20was%20certified.%20However%2C%20the%20company%20has%20appealed.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%3E%3Cstrong%3EWhat%20union%20are%20Amazon%20workers%20joining%3F%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EWorkers%20at%20an%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fi-worked-at-an-amazon-warehouse-before-christmas-exhausting-cried-2022-12%5C%22%3EAmazon%20warehouse%3C%2Fa%3E%20on%20Staten%20Island%20voted%20to%20join%20the%20Amazon%20Labor%20Union.%20In%20other%20instances%2C%20workers%20have%20tried%20to%20organize%20to%20join%20other%20unions.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%3E%3Cstrong%3EWhat%20will%20happen%20if%20Amazon%20unionized%3F%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EAccording%20to%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fmarkets.businessinsider.com%2Fnews%2Fstocks%2Famazon-s-unionization-would-hit-its-profitability-morgan-stanley-says-1031331042%5C%22%3EMorgan%20Stanley%3C%2Fa%3E%C2%A0analysts%2C%20unionization%20at%20Amazon%20could%20increase%20costs%20for%20the%20company.%20By%20increasing%20hourly%20wages%20for%20the%20employees%20in%20Staten%20Island%20who%20voted%20to%20unionize%2C%20Amazon's%20operating%20expenses%20would%20increase%20by%20%24203%20million%20in%202023%20%E2%80%94%20however%2C%20it's%20a%20small%20portion%20of%20the%20company's%20annual%20operating%20expenses%2C%20which%20reached%20%24445%20billion%20in%202021.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EFor%20every%201%25%20of%20Amazon's%20workforce%20that%20unionizes%2C%20analysts%20expect%20it%20to%20lead%20to%20an%20incremental%20%24150%20million%20in%20annual%20operating%20expenses.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cdiv%3ERead%20the%20original%20article%20on%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Famazon-labor-union%5C%22%3EBusiness%20Insider%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1697532001000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F6370fe1ef5877200181ca150%3Fformat%3Djpeg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Famazon-labor-union%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22The%20Amazon%20Labor%20Union's%20Staten%20Island%20win%20was%20called%20the%20biggest%20labor%20victory%20in%20decades.%20Learn%20more%20about%20its%20significance%2C%20challenges%20and%20leaders.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22insider%40insider.com%20(Erica%20Sweeney)%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A5%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Famazon-labor-union%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22On%20Adoption%20Rights%20For%20Queer%20Couples%2C%203%20Of%205%20Supreme%20Court%20Judges%20Say%20'No'%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%3Cp%3EThe%20Supreme%20Court%20judgment%20on%20same-sex%20marriages%20raised%20hope%20on%20allowing%20adoption%20by%20unmarried%20and%20queer%20couples%2C%20only%20for%20it%20to%20be%20dashed%20minutes%20later%20when%20three%20of%20the%20five%20judges%20on%20the%20bench%20disagreed%20with%20Chief%20Justice%20Of%20India%20DY%20Chandrachud%20and%20Justice%20SK%20Kaul%20on%20the%20issue.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EAs%20he%20began%20reading%20out%20his%20judgment%2C%20Chief%20Justice%20DY%20Chandrachud%20said%20the%20five-judge%20bench%20would%20deliver%20four%20separate%20judgments%20and%20%26quot%3Bthere%20is%20a%20degree%20of%20agreement%20and%20a%20degree%20of%20disagreement%26quot%3B%20between%20the%20judges.%20The%20disagreement%2C%20he%20said%2C%20was%20on%20how%20far%20the%20court%20should%20go.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EThe%20bench%20is%20headed%20by%20the%20Chief%20Justice%20and%20also%20comprises%20Justices%20Sanjay%20Kishan%20Kaul%2C%20S%20Ravindra%20Bhat%2C%20Hima%20Kohli%20and%20PS%20Narasimha.%20As%20the%20judgments%20began%20to%20be%20read%20out%2C%20it%20became%20clear%20that%20the%20judges%20agreed%20that%20granting%20legal%20recognition%20to%20same-sex%20marriages%20was%20an%20issue%20best%20left%20to%20the%20legislature%20and%20that%20the%20Special%20Marriages%20Act%20could%20not%20be%20read%20down.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EThey%20also%20asked%20the%20Centre%20to%20proceed%20with%20the%20formation%20of%20a%20committee%20to%20address%20practical%20concerns%20of%20same-sex%20couples%2C%20such%20as%20getting%20ration%20cards%2C%20pension%2C%20gratuity%20and%20succession%20issues.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EA%20crucial%20area%20where%20the%20judges%20disagreed%2C%20however%2C%20was%20whether%20unmarried%20and%20queer%20couples%20had%20the%20right%20to%20jointly%20adopt%20a%20child.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3E'Authority%20Exceeded'%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EReading%20out%20his%20judgment%2C%20Justice%20Chandrachud%20observed%20that%20the%20right%20to%20enter%20into%20a%20union%20cannot%20be%20restricted%20on%20the%20basis%20of%20sexual%20orientation%20and%20ruled%20that%20unmarried%20couples%2C%20including%20queer%20couples%2C%20can%20jointly%20adopt%20a%20child.%20He%20said%20that%20the%20law%20cannot%20assume%20that%20only%20heterosexual%20couples%20can%20be%20good%20parents%20and%20that%20doing%20so%20would%20amount%20to%20discrimination.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EReferring%20to%20the%20Central%20Adoption%20Resource%20Authority%20(CARA)%20guidelines%20for%20adoption%2C%20the%20Chief%20Justice%20said%20the%20Juvenile%20Justice%20Act%20does%20not%20preclude%20unmarried%20couples%20from%20adopting%20and%20the%20Union%20of%20India%20has%20also%20not%20proved%20that%20doing%20so%20is%20in%20the%20best%20interest%20of%20the%20child.%20%26quot%3BSo%20CARA%20has%20exceeded%20its%20authority%20in%20barring%20unmarried%20couples%2C%26quot%3B%20Justice%20Chandrachud%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EStating%20that%20differentiating%20between%20married%20couples%20and%20unmarried%20couples%20has%20no%20%26quot%3Breasonable%20nexus%26quot%3B%20with%20the%20objective%20of%20CARA%2C%20which%20is%20ensuring%20the%20best%20interests%20of%20the%20child%2C%20the%20Chief%20Justice%20said%2C%20%26quot%3BIt%20cannot%20be%20assumed%20that%20unmarried%20couples%20are%20not%20serious%20about%20their%20relationship.%20There%20is%20no%20material%20on%20record%20to%20prove%20that%20only%20a%20married%20heterosexual%20couple%20can%20provide%20stability%20to%20a%20child.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EJustice%20Chandrachud%20also%20noted%20that%20CARA%20Regulation%205(3)%20indirectly%20discriminates%20against%20atypical%20unions.%20%26quot%3BA%20queer%20person%20can%20adopt%20only%20in%20an%20individual%20capacity.%20This%20has%20the%20effect%20of%20reinforcing%20the%20discrimination%20against%20the%20queer%20community%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20said%2C%20adding%20that%20the%20CARA%20circular%20is%20violative%20of%20Article%2015%20of%20the%20Constitution.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EArticle%2015%20prohibits%20discrimination%20on%20grounds%20of%20religion%2C%20race%2C%20caste%2C%20sex%20or%20place%20of%20birth.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EDisagreement%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EWhile%20Justice%20Sanjay%20Kishan%20Kaul%20agreed%20with%20the%20Chief%20Justice%20on%20adoption%2C%20Justice%20Chandrachud%20said%20he%20has%20a%20disagreement%20with%20the%20judgment%20of%20Justice%20S%20Ravindra%20Bhat.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EThe%20Chief%20Justice%20said%20that%2C%20contrary%20to%20Justice%20Bhat's%20judgment%2C%20directions%20in%20his%20judgment%20do%20not%20result%20in%20the%20creation%20of%20an%20institution%20but%20give%20effect%20to%20the%20fundamental%20rights%20under%20Part%20III%20of%20the%20Constitution.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BMy%20learned%20brother%20(Justice%20Bhat)%20also%20acknowledges%20that%20the%20State%20is%20discriminating%20against%20the%20queer%20community%20but%20does%20not%20exercise%20the%20powers%20under%20Article%2032%20to%20alleviate%20their%20plight%2C%26quot%3B%20Justice%20Chandrachud%20said.%20Article%2032%20confers%20powers%20on%20the%20Supreme%20Court%20to%20issue%20orders%20for%20the%20enforcement%20of%20fundamental%20rights.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EMajority%20View%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EIn%20his%20judgment%2C%20which%20is%20the%20majority%20judgment%20since%20Justices%20Hima%20Kohli%20and%20PS%20Narasimha%20agreed%20with%20it%2C%20Justice%20Bhat%20said%20he%20disagreed%20with%20the%20Chief%20Justice%20on%20the%20right%20of%20queer%20couples%20to%20adopt%20and%20that%20he%20had%20certain%20concerns.%20He%20said%20that%20Regulation%205(3)%20of%20CARA%20could%20not%20be%20held%20unconstitutional.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThis%20is%20not%20to%20say%20that%20unmarried%20or%20non-heterosexual%20couples%20can't%20be%20good%20parents..%20..given%20the%20objective%20of%20section%2057%2C%20the%20State%20as%20parens%20patriae%20(legal%20protector)%20has%20to%20explore%20all%20areas%20and%20to%20ensure%20all%20benefits%20reach%20the%20children%20at%20large%20in%20need%20of%20stable%20homes%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20observed.%3C%2Fp%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1697531760000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.ndtvimg.com%2Fi%2F2017-01%2Fadoption-generic_650x400_41484486197.jpg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.ndtv.com%2Findia-news%2Flaw-cant-assume-only-heterosexual-couples-can-be-good-parents-chief-justice-4488048%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22The%20judgment%20on%20same-sex%20marriages%20raised%20hope%20on%20allowing%20adoption%20by%20unmarried%20and%20queer%20couples%2C%20only%20for%20it%20to%20be%20dashed%20minutes%20later%20when%20three%20of%20the%20five%20judges%20on%20the%20bench%20disagreed%20with%20the%20other%20two%20on%20the%20issue.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A0%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.ndtv.com%2Findia-news%2Flaw-cant-assume-only-heterosexual-couples-can-be-good-parents-chief-justice-4488048%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww-ndtv-com.cdn.ampproject.org%2Fc%2Fs%2Fwww.ndtv.com%2Findia-news%2Flaw-cant-assume-only-heterosexual-couples-can-be-good-parents-chief-justice-4488048%2Famp%2F1%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.ndtv.com%2Findia-news%2Flaw-cant-assume