20only%20interpret%20it%20and%20give%20effect%20to%20it.%3C%2Fli%3E%20%3Cli%3EWhether%20a%20change%20in%20the%20regime%20of%20the%20Special%20Marriage%20Act%20is%20for%20the%20Parliament%20to%20decide.%20This%20court%20must%20be%20careful%20to%20not%20enter%20into%20legislative%20domain.%C2%A0%3C%2Fli%3E%20%3Cli%3EIncorrect%20to%20state%20that%20marriage%20is%20a%20static%20and%20unchanging%20institution.%3C%2Fli%3E%20%3Cli%3EQueer%20is%20a%20natural%20phenomenon%20known%20for%20ages.%20Homosexuality%20or%20queerness%20is%20not%20an%20urban%20concept%20or%20restricted%20to%20the%20upper%20classes%20of%20the%20society.%3C%2Fli%3E%20%3Cli%3EOur%20ability%20to%20feel%20love%20and%20connection%20with%20one%20another%20makes%20us%20feel%20human.%20We%20have%20an%20innate%20need%20to%20be%20seen%20and%20see.%20The%20need%20to%20share%20our%20emotions%20make%20us%20who%20we%20are.%20These%20relationships%20may%20take%20many%20forms%2C%20natal%20families%2C%20romantic%20relationships%20etc.%C2%A0%3C%2Fli%3E%20%3Cli%3EThe%20need%20to%20form%20part%20of%20family%20is%20a%20core%20part%20of%20the%20human%20trait%20and%20is%20important%20for%20self%20development.%3C%2Fli%3E%20%3Cli%3EChoosing%20a%20life%20partner%20is%20an%20integral%20part%20of%20choosing%20one's%20course%20of%20life.%20Some%20may%20regard%20this%20as%20the%20most%20important%20decision%20of%20their%20life.%20This%20right%20goes%20to%20the%20root%20of%20the%20right%20to%20life%20and%20liberty%20under%20Article%2021.%C2%A0%C2%A0%20%C2%A0%3C%2Fli%3E%20%3Cli%3EThe%20right%20to%20enter%20into%20union%20includes%20the%20right%20to%20choose%20one's%20partner%20and%20the%20right%20to%20recognition%20of%20that%20union.%20A%20failure%20to%20recognise%20such%20associations%20will%20result%20in%20discrimination%20against%20queer%20couples.%3C%2Fli%3E%20%3Cli%3EAll%20persons%2C%20including%20queer%20persons%2C%20have%20the%20right%20to%20judge%20the%20moral%20quality%20of%20their%20lives.%20The%20meaning%20of%20liberty%20is%20the%20ability%20to%20be%20who%20one%20wishes%20to%20be.%3C%2Fli%3E%20%3Cli%3EThis%20court%20has%20recognized%20that%20queer%20persons%20cannot%20be%20discriminated%20upon.%20Material%20benefits%20and%20services%20flowing%20to%20heterosexual%20couples%20and%20denied%20to%20queer%20couples%20will%20be%20a%20violation%20of%20their%20fundamental%20right.%3C%2Fli%3E%20%3Cli%3E%C2%A0It%20cannot%20be%20assumed%20that%20unmarried%20couples%20are%20not%20serious%20about%20their%20relationship.%3C%2Fli%3E%20%3Cli%3ERight%20to%20enter%20into%20union%20cannot%20be%20restricted%20on%20the%20basis%20of%20sexual%20orientation.%3C%2Fli%3E%20%3Cli%3EWithdrawal%20of%20the%20State%20from%20the%20domestic%20space%20leaves%20the%20vulnerable%20party%20unprotected.%20Thus%2C%20all%20intimate%20activities%20within%20private%20space%20cannot%20be%20said%20to%20be%20beyond%20State's%20scrutiny.%3C%2Fli%3E%20%3Cli%3E%C2%A0Whether%20a%20change%20in%20the%20regime%20of%20the%20Special%20Marriage%20Act%20is%20for%20the%20Parliament%20to%20decide.%20This%20Court%20must%20be%20careful%20to%20not%20enter%20into%20legislative%20domain.%3C%2Fli%3E%20%3Cli%3ECentre%20should%20proceed%20with%20its%20committee%2C%20headed%20by%20the%20Cabinet%20Secretary%2C%20to%20address%20the%20raft%20of%20concerns%20of%20same-sex%20couples%2C%20including%20ration%20cards%2C%20pension%2C%20gratuity%20and%20succession%3C%2Fli%3E%20%3C%2Fol%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EWhat%20Justice%20SK%20Kaul%20Said%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Col%3E%20%3Cli%3ESame-sex%20relationships%20have%20been%20recognized%20from%20antiquity%2C%20not%20just%20for%20sexual%20activities%20but%20as%20relationships%20for%20emotional%20fulfilment.%20I%20have%20referred%20to%20certain%20Sufi%20traditions.%3C%2Fli%3E%20%3Cli%3EThis%20moment%20is%20an%20opportunity%20to%20remedy%20the%20historical%20injustice%20and%20discrimination%20and%20thus%20governance%20needed%20to%20grant%20rights%20to%20such%20unions%20or%20marriages.%3C%2Fli%3E%20%3Cli%3E%C2%A0I%20wholeheartedly%20agree%20with%20the%20Chief%20Justice%20of%20India%20that%20there%20is%20a%20need%20for%20an%20anti-discrimination%20law.%3C%2Fli%3E%20%3Cli%3ELegal%20recognition%20of%20non-heterosexual%20unions%20is%20step%20towards%20marriage%20equality.%3C%2Fli%3E%20%3C%2Fol%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EWhat%20Justice%20S%20Ravindra%20Bhat%20Said%C2%A0%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Col%3E%20%3Cli%3EThis%20Court%20has%20recognized%20that%20marriage%20is%20a%20social%20institution.%20Marriage%20as%20an%20institution%20precedes%20State.%20This%20implies%20that%20marriage%20structure%20exists%20regardless%20of%20the%20State.%20Terms%20of%20marriage%20are%20independent%20of%20the%20State%2C%20and%20its%20sources%20are%20external.%3C%2Fli%3E%20%3Cli%3EThis%20is%20not%20a%20case%20where%20the%20Court%20can%20require%20the%20State%20to%20create%20a%20legal%20status.%20Recognition%20for%20Civil%20union%20cannot%20exist%20in%20the%20absence%20of%20a%20legislation.%20Creation%20of%20an%20institution%20depends%20on%20State%20action%20which%20is%20sought%20to%20be%20compelled%20through%20the%20agency%20of%20the%20Court.%3C%2Fli%3E%20%3Cli%3EAll%20queer%20persons%20have%20the%20right%20to%20choose%20their%20partners.%20But%20State%20cannot%20be%20obligated%20to%20recognize%20the%20bouquet%20of%20rights%20flowing%20from%20such%20a%20Union.%20We%20disagree%20with%20the%20CJI%20on%20this%20aspect.%3C%2Fli%3E%20%3Cli%3ETo%20create%20an%20overarching%20obligation%20upon%20the%20State%20is%20not%20rooted%20in%20any%20past%20decision%20or%20jurisprudence%20but%20queer%20people%20have%20the%20right%20to%20cohabit%20without%20disturbance%20and%20thus%20to%20live%20without%20threat%20flows%20from%20that.%3C%2Fli%3E%20%3Cli%3EDenial%20of%20benefits%20such%20as%20a%20PF%2C%20ESI%2C%20pension%20etc%20to%20queer%20partners%20may%20have%20an%20adverse%20discriminatory%20effect.%C2%A0%3C%2Fli%3E%20%3C%2Fol%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1697525940000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3