%22Most%20American%20men%20see%20their%20earnings%20plateau%20after%2035%20%E2%80%94%20but%20not%20the%20top%202%25%2C%20says%20an%20economist%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%222593%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22Senior%20man%20giving%20an%20explanation%20to%20colleagues%20stock%20photo%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F652e0d4c55f52b01b360f467%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%221945%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EMost%20American%20men%20see%20their%20earnings%20plateau%20after%2035%20%E2%80%94%20but%20not%20the%20top%202%25%2C%20says%20an%20economist%3Cp%3EGetty%20Images%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cul%3E%20%3Cli%3ETop-earning%20US%20men%20experience%20an%20%26quot%3Bastonishing%20surge%20in%20earnings%26quot%3B%20between%20the%20ages%20of%2035%20and%2045.%3C%2Fli%3E%20%3Cli%3EThat's%20according%20to%20an%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.stlouisfed.org%2Fon-the-economy%2F2023%2Foct%2Ftop-earners-see-strong-pay-growth-beyond-age-35%5C%22%3Eanalysis%3C%2Fa%3E%20written%20by%20economist%20Serdar%20Ozkan%20and%20published%20Monday.%3C%2Fli%3E%20%3Cli%3EThe%20top%202%25%20average%20around%20%24400%2C000%20a%20year%20across%20their%20working%20lives%2C%20while%20median%20earners%20earn%20%2450%2C000%20annually%2C%20per%20the%20post.%3C%2Fli%3E%20%3C%2Ful%3E%3Cp%3ETop-earning%20American%20men%20experience%20an%20%26quot%3Bastonishing%20surge%20in%20earnings%26quot%3B%20between%20the%20ages%20of%2035%20and%2045%20while%20other%20men%20see%20their%20incomes%20plateau%2C%20according%20to%20an%C2%A0%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.stlouisfed.org%2Fon-the-economy%2F2023%2Foct%2Ftop-earners-see-strong-pay-growth-beyond-age-35%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eanalysis%3C%2Fa%3E%20by%20economist%20Serdar%20Ozkan%20published%20Monday.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAmerican%20men%20in%20the%20top%202%25%20of%20earners%20saw%20their%20earnings%20increase%20by%20150%25%20between%20the%20ages%20of%2035%20and%2045%2C%20wrote%20Ozkan%2C%20who%20is%20an%20economic%20policy%20advisor%20at%20the%20Federal%20Reserve%20Bank%20of%20St.%20Louis.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EOn%20the%20other%20hand%2C%20the%20median%20and%20the%20bottom%202%25%20of%20male%20earners%20only%20saw%20a%2015%25%20growth%20between%20the%20ages%20of%2035%20and%2045.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EMost%20workers%20see%20the%20bulk%20of%20their%20wage%20increases%20in%20the%20first%20decade%20of%20their%20careers%2C%20and%20wages%20grow%20minimally%20or%20plateau%20after%20the%20age%20of%2035%2C%20wrote%20Ozkan.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BIn%20contrast%2C%20high-earning%20individuals%20continue%20to%20witness%20income%20increases%2C%20albeit%20at%20a%20declining%20pace%2C%20extending%20until%20age%2055%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20added.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EOzkan's%20analysis%20is%20based%20on%20male%20wage%20data%20from%20Internal%20Revenue%20Service%20tax%20forms%20filed%20between%201978%20and%202013%2C%20tracking%20how%20their%20wages%20have%20changed%20between%20the%20ages%20of%2025%20and%2055.%20The%20study%20focuses%20on%20men%20due%20to%20challenges%20in%20getting%20uninterrupted%20earning%20histories%20for%20women%2C%20per%20the%20author.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20difference%20in%20wage%20growth%20is%20starker%20earlier%20in%20life.%20From%20ages%2025%20to%2035%2C%20top%20earners%20experience%20a%20435%25%20rise%20in%20earnings%2C%20compared%20to%20a%2065%25%20increase%20for%20median%20earners.%20The%20lowest%20earners%20see%20only%20a%2016%25%20growth%20in%20this%20period.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EOverall%2C%20this%20means%20the%20lowest%20earners%20earn%20an%20average%20annual%20income%20of%20%2415%2C000%20%E2%80%94%20adjusted%20for%202005%20dollars%20%E2%80%94%20across%20their%20working%20lives%2C%20per%20the%20study.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIn%20comparison%2C%20median%20earners%20average%20%2450%2C000%20annually%20across%20their%20working%20lives%2C%20while%20the%20top%202%25%20earn%20about%20%24400%2C000%20annually%20in%20the%20same%20period.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EA%20previous%20study%C2%A0by%20the%20Washington-based%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fwealth-gap-rich-poor-americans-saps-economic-gdp-growth-billions-2022-5%5C%22%3EEconomic%20Policy%20Institute%3C%2Fa%3E%20on%20wage%20inequality%20published%20in%202022%20showed%20that%20the%20top%2010%25%20of%20earners%20%E2%80%94%20including%20both%20men%20and%20women%20%E2%80%94%20are%20the%20only%20group%20to%20have%20seen%20their%20income%20share%20grow%20since%201979.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EHowever%2C%20the%20pandemic%20also%20saw%20bottom%20earners%20enjoying%20higher%20wage%20growth%20than%20top%20earners%20in%20percentage%20terms%20between%20January%202020%20and%20September%202022%2C%20according%20to%20a%C2%A0%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.nber.org%2Fsystem%2Ffiles%2Fworking_papers%2Fw31010%2Fw31010.pdf%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3ENational%20Bureau%20of%20Economic%20Research%3C%2Fa%3E%20paper%20published%20in%20March.%20However%2C%20these%20increases%20have%20been%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fthe-us-inequality-gap-is-quietly-getting-smaller-2023-7%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eshort-lived%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20per%20the%20Federal%20Reserve%20Bank%20of%20Atlanta.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EOzkan%20did%20not%20immediately%20respond%20to%20a%20request%20for%20comment%20from%20Insider%2C%20sent%20outside%20regular%20business%20hours.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cdiv%3ERead%20the%20original%20article%20on%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Ftop-earning-men-astonishing-wage-growth-after-35-economist-2023-10%5C%22%3EBusiness%20Insider%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1697519711000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F652e0d4c55f52b01b360f467%3Fformat%3Djpeg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Ftop-earning-men-astonishing-wage-growth-after-35-economist-2023-10%22%2C%22summ