D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fberkeley-law-professor-tells-firms-not-to-hire-antisemitic-students-2023-10%5C%22%3EBusiness%20Insider%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1697514213000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F652de18e6561dd877e7c00d3%3Fformat%3Djpeg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fberkeley-law-professor-tells-firms-not-to-hire-antisemitic-students-2023-10%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22%26quot%3BWhen%20students%20face%20consequences%20for%20their%20actions%2C%20they%20straighten%20up%2C%26quot%3B%20said%20University%20of%20California%20Berkeley%20law%20professor%20Steven%20Davidoff%20Solomon.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22ktan%40insider.com%20(Kwan%20Wei%20Kevin%20Tan)%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A10%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fberkeley-law-professor-tells-firms-not-to-hire-antisemitic-students-2023-10%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22Irish%20HC%20Questions%20India's%20Handling%20of%20Mob%20Violence%20While%20Hearing%20Mumbai%20Meat%20Trader's%20Asylum%20Plea%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%3Cimg%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F10%2F17090551%2F253198387_ac683776ab_h.jpg%5C%22%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3ELondon%3A%3C%2Fstrong%3E%20In%20a%20significant%20development%2C%20a%20wealthy%20meat%20trader%20from%20Mumbai%20has%20sought%20asylum%20in%20Ireland%2C%20citing%20attacks%20and%20threats%20from%20cow%20vigilantes%20in%20India.%20The%20case%2C%20which%20came%20to%20light%20through%20a%20judgment%20issued%20by%20the%20High%20Court%20of%20Ireland%20in%20October%202022%2C%20highlights%20the%20growing%20concern%20over%20incidents%20of%20mob%20violence%20in%20India%20and%20the%20response%20of%20the%20state%20machinery%2C%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.newslaundry.com%2F2023%2F10%2F16%2Fexclusive-mumbai-meat-traders-quest-for-asylum-in-ireland-over-attack-sweeping-cow-vigilantism%5C%22%3Ereports%3C%2Fa%3E%20%3Cem%3ENewslaundry%3C%2Fem%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EAccording%20to%20the%20court%20order%2C%20the%20individual%20in%20question%2C%20whose%20identity%20has%20not%20been%20disclosed%20as%20it%20is%20the%20rule%20for%20people%20applying%20for%20international%20protection%2C%20is%20in%20his%2040s%20and%20possesses%20assets%20valued%20at%20four%20million%20euros%2C%20alongside%20his%20two%20sons.%20In%202017%2C%20he%20was%20attacked%20by%20unknown%20people%2C%20allegedly%20belonging%20to%20the%20Rashtriya%20Swayamsevak%20Sangh%20and%20%E2%80%98cow%20vigilantes%E2%80%99%2C%20who%20shut%20his%20business%20and%20ordered%20him%20to%20%E2%80%9Cconvert%20to%20Hinduism.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EWhile%20the%20International%20Protection%20Appeals%20Tribunal%20initially%20denied%20the%20asylum%20request%2C%20Justice%20Siobhan%20Phelan%20overturned%20this%20decision%20and%20remanded%20it%20for%20reconsideration%20by%20a%20new%20tribunal%20member.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EAbbey%20Law%2C%20the%20legal%20firm%20representing%20the%20meat%20trader%2C%20told%20%3Cem%3ENewslaundry%3C%2Fem%3E%20that%20the%20%E2%80%9Creconsideration%20has%20not%20yet%20taken%20place%E2%80%9D.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EWhile%20the%20final%20decision%20is%20still%20pending%2C%20it%E2%80%99s%20worth%20noting%20that%20asylum%20cases%20originating%20from%20India%20are%20uncommon.%20Nevertheless%2C%20the%20court%E2%80%99s%20insights%20in%20this%20specific%20case%20serve%20as%20a%20valuable%20guide%20to%20how%20Western%20democracies%E2%80%99%20legal%20systems%20are%20grappling%20with%20allegations%20of%20%E2%80%9Creligious%20persecution%20by%20Hindu%20nationalists%E2%80%9D%20in%20India.%20Even%20though%20the%20final%20decision%20remains%20pending%2C%20cases%20of%20asylum%20from%20India%20are%20relatively%20rare.%20However%2C%20the%20court%E2%80%99s%20observations%20in%20this%20particular%20instance%2C%20along%20with%20its%20historical%20context%2C%20offer%20a%20blueprint%20for%20understanding%20how%20judicial%20systems%20in%20Western%20democracies%20are%20responding%20to%20allegations%20of%20%E2%80%9Creligious%20persecutions%20at%20the%20hands%20of%20Hindu%20nationalists%E2%80%9D%20in%20India.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EIn%20Ireland%2C%20the%20International%20Protection%20Office%20(IPO)%20evaluates%20applications%20for%20international%20protection%2C%20considering%20cases%20from%20both%20conflict-ridden%20and%20ostensibly%20safe%20countries.%20In%202019%2C%20the%20IPO%20initially%20denied%20asylum%20to%20the%20Indian%20trader%2C%20asserting%20that%20state%20protection%20was%20available%20in%20India.%20Subsequent%20appeals%20led%20to%20the%20International%20Protection%20Appeals%20Tribunal%20(IPAT)%20acknowledging%20the%20lack%20of%20state%20protection%20and%20police%20reluctance%20to%20prosecute%20his%20attackers%20but%20arguing%20that%20the%20trader%20could%20relocate%20within%20India.%20However%2C%20a%20judicial%20review%20in%202020%20quashed%20the%20%E2%80%9Cinternal%20protection%20alternative%E2%80%9D%20finding.%20During%20reconsideration%2C%20the%20trader%E2%80%99s%20efforts%20to%20change%20his%20profession%20were%20viewed%20skeptically%20by%20the%20IPAT%2C%20which%20ultimately%20upheld%20the%20internal%20protection%20alternative%20in%20March%202021.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EThe%20Mumbai%20meat%20trader%2C%20dissatisfied%20with%20the%20second%20ruling%20from%20IPAT%2C%20took%20his%20case%20back%20to%20the%20High%20Court%20of%20Ireland%2C%20where%20Justice%20Burns%20approved%20a%20judicial%20review%20in%20April%202021.%20Justice%20Burns%20recognised%20the%20case%E2%80%99s%20merit%20and%20remitted%20it%20to%20the%20IPAT%20for%20reconsideration.%20However%2C%20this%20time%2C%20both%20the%20IPAT%20and%20the%20Ministry%20of%20Justice%20in%20Ireland%20opposed%20the%20court%E2%80%99s%20decision%2C%20arguing%20that%20there%20was%20no%20need%20to%20change%20the%20%E2%80%9Cinternal%20protection%20alternative%E2%80%9D%20finding.%20Subsequently%2C%20Justice%20Siobhan%20Phelan%20presided%20over%20the%20case%20and%20considered%20arguments%20from%20the%20trader%2C%20the%20IPAT%2C%20and%20the%20Ministry%20of%20Justice.%20In%20her%20deliberation%2C%20she%20referred%20to%20a%20similar%20asylum%20case%20involving%20another%20Mumbai%20meat%20trader%20in%20Canada%20and%20stressed%20the%20importance%20of%20assessing%20the%20cumulative%20nature%20of%20persecution%20against%20Muslims%20in%20India%2C%20implying%20a%20need%20to%20determine%20whether%20persecution%20was%20widespread%20or%20localised%20in%20the%20country.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EThis%20kind%20of%20asylum%20seeking%20seems%20to%20be%20the%20first%20case%20in%20Europe.%20However%2C%20in%202018%2C%20a%20muslim%20beef%20trader%20from%20Mumbai%20was%20granted%20refugee%20status%20in%20Canada%20noting%20that%20there%20was%20a%20%E2%80%9Csubjective%20fear%20of%20persecution%20in%20India%20as%20a%20Muslim%E2%80%9D%20and%20as%20someone%20involved%20in%20the%20industry%20in%20India.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EAt%20the%20very%C2%A0%20first%2C%20Justice%20Phelan%20pointed%20out%20various%20shortcomings%20in%20the%20IPAT%E2%80%99s%20decision.%20%E2%80%9CIt%20is%20my%20view%20that%20the%20existence%20of%20cow%20vigilantism%20throughout%20India%20needed%20to%20be%20considered%20cumulatively%20with%20the%20other%20evidence%20of%20discriminatory%20or%20persecutory%20treatment%20of%20Muslims%20in%20assessing%20whether%20it%20was%20reasonable%20to%20expect%20the%20applicant%20and%20his%20family%20to%20relocate%20to%20the%20identified%20areas.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CThe%20IPAT%20decision%20does%20not%20demonstrate%20that%20the%20IPAT%20approached%20the%20question%20of%20whether%20alternative%20protection%20was%20reasonably%20available%20by%20considering%20whether%20the%20applicant%2C%20a%20man%20in%20his%2040s%2C%20had%20decided%20to%20cease%20work%20or%20change%20profession%20solely%20in%20order%20to%20avoid%20further%20incidents%20of%20persecution%20and%20thereafter%20assessing%20whether%20the%20need%20to%20change%20work%20could%20in%20itself%2C%20and%20on%20the%20facts%20of%20this%20case%2C%20potentially%20constitute%20persecution%20before%20refusing%20protection%20on%20the%20basis%20of%20a%20reasoned%20conclusion%20that%20the%20change%20of%20profession%20in%20the%20event%20of%20a%20return%20to%20a%20different%20part%20of%20India%20did%20not%20constitute%20persecution.%20Through%20its%20failure%20to%20conduct%20this%20analysis%2C%20I%20am%20satisfied%20that%20the%20IPAT%20has%20erred%20in%20law%20in%20its%20identification%20of%20the%20legal%20test%20to%20be%20applied%20in%20deciding%20that%20a%20reasonable%20internal%20protection%20alternative%20is%20available%20to%20the%20applicant.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EThe%20judge%20also%20found%20it%20%E2%80%9Cconcerning%E2%80%9D%20that%20the%20IPAT%2C%20while%20proposing%20the%20internal%20protection%20alternative%2C%20failed%20to%20assess%20the%20risk%20for%20Muslims%20associated%20with%20beef%20trade%20in%20India.%20%E2%80%9CI%20am%20confirmed%20in%20my%20conclusion%20that%20the%20decision%20is%20unsustainable%20in%20law%2C%E2%80%9D%20she%20concluded.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fauthor%2Fkalrav-joshi%5C%22%3E%3Cem%3EKalrav%20Joshi%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cem%3E%20is%20a%20London-based%20journalist-writer.%20He%20writes%20on%20politics%2C%20culture%2C%20technology%20and%20culture.%20%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1697513875000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F10%2F17090551%2F253198387_ac683776ab_h.jpg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fcommunalism%2Firish-hc-questions-indias-handling-of-mob-violence-while-hearing-mumbai-meat-traders-asylum-plea%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22A%20Mumbai%20meat%20trader's%20asylum%20case%20in%20Ireland%2C%20currently%20awaiting%20reconsideration%2C%20serves%20as%20an%20illustration%20of%20how%20judicial%20systems%20in%20Western%20democracies%20are%20responding%20to%20allegations%20of%20%E2%80%