%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.insider.com%2Fscientists-running-out-of-places-to-let-dead-whales-decompose-2019-6%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Egray%20whale%20strandings%3C%2Fa%3E%20from%20Mexico%20all%20the%20way%20to%20Alaska%20have%20been%20declared%20an%20%26quot%3Bunusual%20mortality%20event%2C%26quot%3B%20or%20a%20significant%20die-off%20of%20a%20species%20that%20is%20unexplained%20and%20requires%20a%20quick%20response.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ETwo%20other%20mass%20die-offs%20of%20gray%20whales%20occurred%20in%20the%201980s%20and%201990s%2C%20though%20those%20only%20lasted%20a%20couple%20of%20years%3B%20the%20latest%20is%20still%20ongoing.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20latest%20die-off%20has%20caused%20the%20North%20Pacific%20gray%20whale%20population%20to%20plummet%20from%20an%20estimated%2027%2C000%20in%202016%20to%2014%2C500%20in%202023%2C%20according%20to%20the%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.fisheries.noaa.gov%2Ffeature-story%2Fnew-gray-whale-count-shows-further-decline-hints-turnaround%23%3A~%3Atext%3DNOAA%2520Fisheries%2520declared%2520an%2520Unusual%2Cto%2520approximately%252014%252C500%2520in%25202023.%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3ENational%20Oceanic%20and%20Atmospheric%20Administration%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EFor%20years%2C%20researchers%20could%20only%20guess%20what%20was%20killing%20the%20whales.%20NOAA%20has%20previously%20noted%20that%20emaciation%20had%20been%20observed%20in%20some%20of%20the%20dead%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fvideo-false-killer-whale-twirls-divers-species-bring-humans-fish-2023-10%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ewhales%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20but%20not%20in%20others.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBut%20scientists%20at%20Oregon%20State%20University's%20Marine%20Mammal%20Institute%20now%20say%20there%20is%20strong%20evidence%20that%20the%20whale%20deaths%20are%20linked%20directly%20to%20sea%20ice%20melting%20in%20the%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Farctic-regions-changing-to-rainfall-instead-of-snow-2022-12%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EArctic%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20according%20to%20a%20study%20published%20Thursday%20in%20the%20journal%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.science.org%2Fdoi%2F10.1126%2Fscience.adi1847%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EScience%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EJoshua%20Stewart%2C%20an%20assistant%20professor%20at%20the%20Marine%20Mammal%20Institute%20and%20lead%20author%20of%20the%20study%2C%20said%20the%20decrease%20in%20sea%20ice%20was%20also%20causing%20the%20gray%20whales'%20food%20supply%20to%20diminish.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BFeels%20like%20this%20time%20we've%20got%20a%20pretty%20good%20'smoking%20gun%2C%26quot%3B%20Stewart%20told%20the%20outlet%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.youtube.com%2Fwatch%3Fv%3DKp9PxNca-J4%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EKTVB%3C%2Fa%3E%20of%20the%20explanation%20of%20what%20was%20causing%20the%20whale%20deaths.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EGray%20whales%20make%20the%20longest%20migration%20of%20any%20mammal%20on%20Earth%2C%20traveling%20more%20than%2012%2C000%20miles%20every%20year%20from%20their%20foraging%20grounds%20in%20the%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fbeavers-invade-alaska-arctic-tundra-photos-satellite-images-damage-2023-1%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EArctic%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20where%20they%20spend%20the%20summers%2C%20to%20their%20breeding%20grounds%20in%20the%20warm%2C%20shallow%20lagoons%20of%20Mexico's%20Baja%20Peninsula%2C%20where%20they%20spend%20the%20winters.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWhile%20in%20the%20Arctic%2C%20the%20gray%20whales%20feed%20on%20amphipod%20crustaceans.%20Amphipods%20in%20turn%20feed%20on%20algae%2C%20which%20grows%20on%20the%20underside%20of%20sea%20ice.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BWith%20less%20ice%2C%20you%20get%20less%20algae%2C%20which%20is%20worse%20for%20the%20gray%20whale%20prey%2C%26quot%3B%20Stewart%20said%20in%20a%20release%20from%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Ftoday.oregonstate.edu%2Fnews%2Fgray-whales-experience-major-population-swings-result-arctic-conditions-research-shows%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EOregon%20State%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20adding%2C%20%26quot%3BWhen%20there%20are%20sudden%20declines%20in%20the%20quality%20of%20prey%2C%20the%20population%20of%20gray%20whales%20is%20significantly%20affected.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIn%20other%20words%2C%20the%20melting%20sea%20ice%20disrupts%20the%20entire%20food%20chain.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20decrease%20in%20available%20food%20can%20cause%20skinnier%20or%20malnourished%20whales%2C%20as%20well%20as%20lower%20birth%20rates.%20Stewart%20said%20he%20does%20not%20think%20there%20is%20currently%20a%20risk%20of%20extinction%20for%20gray%20whales.%20The%20species%2C%20which%20was%20hunted%20to%20the%20brink%20of%20extinction%20decades%20ago%2C%20has%20been%20touted%20has%20a%20major%20conservation%20success%20thanks%20to%20the%20populations%20bouncing%20back%20after%20international%20whaling%20regulations%20were%20enacted.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBut%20the%20die-offs%20are%20a%20reminder%20of%20the%20wide-ranging%20impacts%20of%20the%20climate%20crisis%2C%20as%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fsea-ice-levels-in-antarctica-reached-a-new-historic-low-2023-9%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Esea%20ice%20continues%20to%20melt%3C%2Fa%3E%20at%20alarming%20and%20historic%20rates.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BEven%20highly%20mobile%2C%20long-lived%20species%20such%20as%20gray%20whales%20are%20sensitive%20to%20climate%20change%20impacts%2C%26quot%3B%20Stewart%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAnd%20while%20he%20said%20we%20probably%20do%20not%20have%20to%20worry%20about%20extinction%2C%20we%20may%20have%20to%20simply%20get%20used%20to%20having%20fewer%20gray%20whales.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cdiv%3ERead%20the%20original%20article%20on%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fgray-whale-deaths-linked-to-melting-sea-ice-arctic-study-2023-10%5C%22%3EBusiness%20Insider%3C%2