rvices'%20status%20and%20how%20to%20mitigate%20issues%20if%20you're%20affected%20today%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%224864%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22The%20logo%20of%20Amazon%20Web%20Services%20(AWS)%20is%20seen%20during%20the%204th%20annual%20America%20Digital%20Latin%20American%20Congress%20of%20Business%20and%20Technology%20in%20Santiago%2C%20Chile%2C%20September%205%2C%202018.%20REUTERS%2FIvan%20Alvarado%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F5fbc4e5632f2170011f70ce3%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%223648%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3E%3Cp%3EReuters%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cul%3E%20%3Cli%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fhow-amazon-web-services-expanded-cloud-empire-beyond-infrastructure-2021-3%5C%22%3EAmazon%20Web%20Services%3C%2Fa%3E%20is%20a%20cloud%20service%20offered%20by%20Amazon.%3C%2Fli%3E%20%3Cli%3EOutages%20can%20be%20tracked%20by%20Downdetector%20and%20Amazon's%20own%20AWS%20dashboard.%C2%A0%3C%2Fli%3E%20%3Cli%3EMany%20popular%20businesses%20from%20streaming%20companies%20like%20Netflix%20to%20Google%20and%20Slack%20are%20AWS%20customers.%C2%A0%3C%2Fli%3E%20%3C%2Ful%3E%3Cp%3EAmazon%20Web%20Services%20%E2%80%94%20known%20more%20commonly%20as%20AWS%20%E2%80%94%20is%20a%20cloud%20computing%20service%20that%20lets%20businesses%20rent%20online%20storage%20and%20computing%20power%20as%20a%20service.%20Its%20relative%20affordability%20and%20flexibility%20makes%20AWS%20a%20popular%20resource%20for%20all%20sorts%20of%20server%20needs%2C%20including%20storage%2C%20data%20management%2C%20AI%2C%20game%20and%20mobile%20development%2C%20and%20more.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EHere's%20more%20about%20AWS%2C%20including%20how%20to%20tell%20when%20your%20AWS%20system%20is%20offline%20or%20suffering%20an%20outage.%C2%A0%20%C2%A0%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%3EWhat%20does%20AWS%20stand%20for%3F%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EAWS%20stands%20for%20Amazon%20Web%20Services.%20It's%20Amazon's%20subsidiary%2C%20offering%20on-demand%20cloud%20computing%20services%20on%20a%20pay-as-you-go%20subscription%20basis.%C2%A0%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%3EIs%20Amazon%20AWS%20down%20right%20now%3F%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EIf%20you're%20an%20AWS%20user%20and%20encountering%20connectivity%20issues%2C%20there%20may%20be%20an%20outage.%20A%20dependable%20way%20to%20check%20on%20the%20status%20of%20AWS%20in%20real%20time%20is%20to%20check%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fdowndetector.com%2Fstatus%2Faws-amazon-web-services%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EDowndetector%3C%2Fa%3E.%20The%20site's%20AWS%20status%20page%20shows%20a%20rolling%20graph%20of%20reported%20issues%20and%20an%20overall%20assessment%20of%20whether%20the%20system%20is%20up%20or%20down.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%3EWhat%20was%20the%20last%20AWS%20outage%3F%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EWhile%20Downdetector's%20AWS%20status%20page%20can%20help%20you%20see%20all%20the%20reported%20AWS%20performance%20issues%20over%20the%20preceding%2024%20hours%2C%20Amazon's%20own%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fhealth.aws.amazon.com%2Fhealth%2Fstatus%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EAWS%20Health%20Dashboard%3C%2Fa%3E%20lets%20you%20find%20much%20more%20granular%20results%20over%20a%20longer%20timeframe.%20If%20there%20was%20an%20outage%20anytime%20in%20the%20last%2012%20months%2C%20you%20can%20browse%20AWS%20by%20service%20name%20or%20region%20and%20see%20all%20reported%20outages.%20If%20there's%20a%20service%20for%20which%20you%20want%20to%20see%20real-time%20status%20notifications%2C%20you%20can%20subscribe%20to%20its%20RSS%20feed%20from%20this%20dashboard%20as%20well.%C2%A0%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%3EWhat%20companies%20are%20affected%20by%20AWS%20outages%3F%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EWhile%20AWS%20outages%20are%20rare%2C%20when%20they%20happen%2C%20they%20can%20broadly%20impact%20many%20users.%20That's%20because%20many%20popular%20websites%20and%20services%20rely%20on%20AWS%20for%20storage%20and%20computing%20needs.%20Popular%20video%20streaming%20services%20like%20Netflix%2C%20Hulu%2C%20and%20Disney%2B%20use%20AWS%2C%20for%20example%2C%20and%20in%20recent%20AWS%20outages%2C%20those%20services%20were%20unavailable%2C%20or%20streaming%20was%20intermittent%20for%20many%20subscribers.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBut%20AWS%20is%20also%20used%20by%20many%20other%20businesses%2C%20with%20roughly%20a%20third%20of%20the%20internet%20running%20on%20AWS%20servers%2C%20according%20to%20Statista.%20Fast%20food%20chains%20like%20McDonald's%20and%20Burger%20King%20briefly%20lost%20their%20ability%20to%20manage%20online%20and%20mobile%20app%20ordering%20in%20a%20previous%20AWS%20outage.%20Gamers%20using%20the%20PlayStation%20Network%20have%20been%20affected%2C%20as%20well%20as%20Slack%20and%20Google.%20The%20bottom%20line%20is%20that%20AWS%20outages%20can%20impact%20some%20of%20the%20largest%20and%20most%20popular%20companies.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%3EHow%20do%20I%20mitigate%20an%20AWS%20outage%3F%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20good%20news%20is%20that%20AWS%20outages%20are%20rare.%20AWS%20is%20built%20on%20an%20infrastructure%20that%20allows%20different%20regions%20to%20operate%20independently%2C%20so%20an%20outage%20in%20one%20region%20generally%20does%20not%20affect%20others.%20If%20you%20subscribe%20to%20an%20AWS%20service%2C%20depending%20on%20which%20level%20of%20service%20you%20choose%2C%20Amazon%20may%20be%20bound%20to%20a%20service-level%20agreement%20that%20guarantees%20a%20high%20level%20of%20uptime%2C%20which%20can%20be%20as%20high%20as%2099.99%25.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EEven%20so%2C%20as%20an%20AWS%20customer%2C%20you%20need%20to%20take%20steps%20to%20mitigate%20issues%20when%20outages%20occur.%20This%20includes%20having%20a%20robust%20disaster%20recovery%20plan%2C%20dependable%20backup%20strategy%2C%20and%20data%20replication%20that%20lets%20you%20rebound%20from%20outages%20quickly%20and%20efficiently.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%3EWhy%20are%20many%20businesses%20moving%20to%20AWS%3F%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EAWS%20is%20a%20compelling%20option%20for%20many%20businesses.%20Not%20only%20is%20it%20a%20global%20service%2C%20available%20in%20more%20than%20240%20countries%2C%20but%20AWS%20is%20segregated%20into%2081%20zones%20that%20allow%20customers%20to%20fence%20their%20services%20into%20geographical%20areas%20and%20scale%20up%20as%20needed.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EMoreover%2C%20AWS%20is%20a%20pay-as-you-go%20service%20with%20no%20long-term%20contracts.%20It%20lets%20businesses%20scale%20as%20quickly%20(or%20slowly)%20as%20desired%20without%20investing%20in%20their%20own%20infrastructure.%20Amazon%20includes%20access%20to%20low-cost%20migration%20services%20to%20move%20to%20AWS%20efficiently%2C%20and%20billing%20is%20precise%20and%20accurate%20%E2%80%94%20users%20don't%20have%20to%20pay%20estimates%20or%20%26quot%3Btrue-up%26quot%3B%20on%20an%20ongoing%20basis.%20Instead%2C%20all%20payments%20are%20on%20a%20rolling%20monthly%20basis.%C2%A0%C2%A0%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EFinally%2C%20it's%20worth%20noting%20that%20thanks%20to%20service-level%20agreements%2C%20Amazon%20ensures%20certain%20levels%20of%20uptime%20while%20offering%20integrated%20security%2C%20privacy%2C%20and%20reliability%20guarantees.%20All%20of%20these%20elements%20would%20be%20costly%20if%20a%20company%20had%20to%20implement%20all%20of%20them%20on%20its%20own.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cdiv%3ERead%20the%20original%20article%20on%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Faws-outage%5C%22%3EBusiness%20Insider%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1697500333000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F5fbc4e5632f2170011f70ce3%3Fformat%3Djpeg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Faws-outage%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22Concerned%20about%20an%20AWS%20outage%3F%20Amazon%20Web%20Services'%20service%20status%20and%20disruptions%20can%20be%20tracked.%20Stay%20ahead%20and%20informed%20with%20the%20latest%20updates.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22insider%40insider.com%20(Dave%20Johnson)%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A23%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Faws-outage%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22Russia%20aims%20to%20pierce%20Ukraine%20defences%20in%20northeast%2C%20general%20says%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%22%2C%22published%22%3A1697499788000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fstatic.toiimg.com%2Fphoto%2Fmsid-104480745%2Cimgsize-24198.cms%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Ftimesofindia.indiatimes.com%2Fworld%2Feurope%2Frussia-aims-to-pierce-ukraine-defences-in-northeast-general-says%2Farticleshow%2F104480645.cms%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22%3Cimg%20border%3D%5C%220%5C%22%20align%3D%5C%22left%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Ftimesofindia.indiatimes.com%2Fphoto%2F104480645.cms%5C%22%20hspace%3D%5C%2210%5C%22%3ERussia%20is%20aiming%20to%20break%20through%20Ukrainian%20defences%20in%20the%20Kupiansk-Lyman%20area%2C%20according%20to%20Ukraine's%20ground%20forces%20commander.%20The%20area%20has%20seen%20a%20sharp%20increase%20in%20fighting%2C%20with%20Russia%20allegedly%20bringing%20in%20staff%20and%20preparing%20for%20offensive%20actions.%20The%20towns%20of%20Kupiansk%20and%20Lyman%20were%20key%20in%20Ukraine's%20efforts%20to%20evict%20Russian%20troops%20from%20the%20Donbas%20industrial%20heartland.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A0%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Ftimesofindia.indiatimes.com%2Fworld%2Feurope%2Frussia-aims-to-pierce-ukraine-defences-in-northeast-general-says%2Farticleshow%2F104480645.cms%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fm-timesofindia-com.cdn.ampproject.org%2Fc%2Fs%2Fm.timesofindia.com%2Fworld%2Feurope%2Frussia-aims-to-pierce-ukraine-defences-in-northeast-general-says%2Famp_articleshow%2F104480645.cms%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fm.timesofindia.com%2Fworld%2Feurope%2Frussia-aims-to-pierce-ukraine-defences-in-northeast-general-says%2Famp_articleshow%2F104480645.cms%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22LinkedIn%20employees%20discovered%20a%20mysterious%20list%20of%20around%20500%20names%20over%20the%20weekend.%20On%20Monday%2C%20workers%20said%20those%20on%20the%20list%20were%20laid%20off.%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%22910%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22LinkedIn%20laid%20off%20over%20600%20staffers%20on%20Monday.%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F652da1c48bed706e837dbc2c%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22682%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3ELinkedIn%20laid%20off%20over%20600%20staffers%20on%20Monday.%3Cp%3EJonathan%20Raa%2FNurPhoto%20via%20Getty%20Images%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cul%3E%20%3Cli%3ESome%20workers%20at%20LinkedIn%20found%20their%20names%20on%20an%20internal%20list%20a%20day%20before%20they%20were%20laid%20off.%3C%2Fli%3E%20%3Cli%3ETwo%20workers%20told%20Insider%20the%20list%20caused%20a%20stir%20as%20workers%20tried%20to%20figure%20out%20if%20they%20were%20on%20it.%3C%2Fli%3E%20%3Cli%3ELinkedIn%20announced%20it%20had%20laid%20off%20more%20than%20600%20employees%20on%20Monday.%3C%2Fli%3E%20%3C%2Ful%3E%3Cp%3ESome%20LinkedIn%20workers%20worried%20they%20were%20about%20to%20be%20laid%20off%20after%20a%20mysterious%20internal%20list%20of%20about%20500%20employees%20was%20discovered%20to%20be%20accessible%20by%20anyone%20at%20the%20company.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EHours%20later%2C%20workers%20who%20had%20seen%20their%20name%20on%20the%20list%20had%20their%20worst%20fears%20confirmed%20%E2%80%94%20they%20were%20laid%20off%2C%20two%20LinkedIn%20workers%20told%20Insider.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EA%20LinkedIn%20worker%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.teamblind.com%2Fpost%2FLinkedIn-Layoff-508-in-Engineering-tWCmUs8h%5C%22%3Eposted%3C%2Fa%3E%20Sunday%20night%20on%20Blind%2C%20an%20anonymous%20job-posting%20site%20that%20verifies%20workers'%20employment%20using%20their%20company%20email%2C%20about%20a%20potential%20%26quot%3Bkill%20list%2C%26quot%3B%20as%20the%20worker%20described%20it%2C%20of%20employees%20that%20would%20be%20impacted%20by%20an%20upcoming%20layoffs.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ERumors%20began%20to%20swirl%20within%20the%20company%20after%20the%20worker's%20post%2C%20two%20employees%20told%20Insider.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20LinkedIn%20worker%20who%20posted%20to%20Blind%20noticed%20a%20new%20list%2C%20called%20%26quot%3BOctoberUpdate%2C%26quot%3B%20had%20been%20created%20by%20the%20company's%20human%20resources%20team%20on%20LinkedIn's%20GroupID%20tool%2C%20a%20third-party%20system%20that%20allows%20workers%20to%20add%20themselves%20and%20others%20to%20teams%20and%20can%20be%20used%20to%20create%20group%20calendar%20events%20or%20email%20chains%2C%20the%20two%20employees%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BI%20was%20getting%20texts%20from%20everybody%2C%20all%20my%20friends%2C%26quot%3B%20one%20of%20the%20LinkedIn%20workers%20told%20Insider.%20%26quot%3BEverybody%20was%20calling%20and%20saying%20'Hey%2C%20check%20GroupID.'%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20LinkedIn%20worker%20said%20the%20list%20included%20hundreds%20of%20people%2C%20including%20a%20friend%20who%20later%20learned%20on%20Monday%20that%20they%20had%20been%20included%20in%20the%20layoffs%20round.%20Insider%20was%20unable%20to%20independently%20confirm%20the%20full%20list%20of%20names%20on%20the%20list%20to%20check%20if%20all%20had%20been%20impacted%20by%20the%20layoffs.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EA%20LinkedIn%20spokesperson%20confirmed%20to%20Insider%20that%20the%20company%20uses%20GroupID%20%26quot%3Bto%20create%20and%20manage%20distribution%20lists.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20spokesperson%20said%20that%20LinkedIn%20is%20%26quot%3Bcommitted%20to%20ensuring%20all%20impacted%20employees%20are%20treated%20with%20care%20and%20respect%26quot%3B%20with%20regards%20to%20the%20layoffs.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20GroupID%20list%20was%20deleted%20the%20same%20day%20after%20dozens%20of%20workers%20took%20to%20the%20company's%20internal%20channel%20to%20ask%20management%20about%20the%20list%2C%20but%20management%20did%20not%20comment%20on%20the%20list%2C%20the%20worker%20told%20Insider.%20Even%20though%20it%20had%20been%20deleted%2C%20LinkedIn%20workers%20could%20still%20see%20the%20history%20of%20the%20list%2C%20including%20the%20names%20on%20it%2C%20the%20worker%20said.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20larger%20GroupID%20tool%20also%20became%20inaccessible%20to%20LinkedIn%20staff%20on%20Sunday%2C%20two%20workers%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BWe've%20heard%20that%20you%20may%20be%20experiencing%20issues%20accessing%20Go%2FGroupID%2C%26quot%3B%20said%20an%20email%20sent%20around%204%20a.m.%20on%20Monday%20from%20the%20company's%20internal%20communications%20team%20that%20was%20viewed%20by%20Insider.%20%26quot%3BWe're%20looking%20into%20it%20and%20appreciate%20your%20patience%20as%20we%20work%20through%20the%20issue.%20There%20is%20no%20ETA%20at%20the%20moment.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIt%20is%20unclear%20why%20the%20internal%20tool%20went%20down.%20The%20two%20LinkedIn%20workers%20told%20Insider%20that%20initially%20the%20tool%20was%20slow%20to%20load%20on%20Sunday%20night%20when%20they%20checked%20it%20and%20they%20suspected%20there%20were%20too%20many%20workers%20trying%20to%20access%20the%20tool%20at%20once.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BIt%20took%20like%2020%20minutes%20for%20the%20tool%20to%20load%2C%26quot%3B%20one%20LinkedIn%20worker%20said%2C%20adding%20that%20the%20tool%20is%20typically%20not%20one%20that%20a%20worker%20uses%20every%20day%2C%20but%20it%20usually%20reserved%20for%20setting%20up%20or%20joining%20different%20groups.%20%26quot%3BIt%20felt%20like%20everyone%20at%20the%20company%20was%20looking%20at%20that%20list%20at%20once.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ELinkedIn%20confirmed%20the%20job%20cuts%20in%20a%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fnews.linkedin.com%2F2023%2Foctober%2Foctober-2023-update%5C%22%3Epress%20release%3C%2Fa%3E%20on%20Monday%20after%20it%20sent%20a%20company%20wide%20email%20announcing%20over%20600%20employees%20would%20be%20impacted%20by%20layoffs%2C%20including%20a%20reduction%