es%20with%20its%20%E2%80%9Cobjectives%E2%80%9D%20in%20connection%20with%20the%20Adani%20group%2C%20the%20report%20said.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EThe%20I-T%20department%20has%20accused%20Oxfam%20India%20of%20being%20%E2%80%9Cinvolved%20in%20the%20activity%20of%20submission%20to%20UN%20Global%20Impact%20to%20delist%20Adani%20Ports%2C%20which%20is%20not%20as%20per%20the%20objects%20of%20the%20assessee%E2%80%9D.%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EIn%20the%20letter%20to%20Environics%20Trust%2C%20the%20department%20said%20that%20the%20trust%20collaborated%20with%20the%20Mineral%20Inheritors%20Right%20Association%20for%20protesting%20against%20Jindal%20Steel%20Works%20and%20Adani%20Coal%20Projects%20in%20Odisha%20and%20that%20it%20was%20%E2%80%9Cnot%20as%20per%20the%20objects%20of%20the%20Trust%E2%80%9D.%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cins%3EAlso%20read%3A%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Freligion%2Famidst-cancellations-of-thousands-of-ngos-licences-ram-mandir-applies-for-fcra-licence%5C%22%3EAmidst%20Cancellations%20Of%20Thousands%20Of%20NGOs%E2%80%99%20Licences%2C%20Ram%20Mandir%20Trust%20Applies%20For%20FCRA%20Licence%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fins%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EApart%20from%20reasons%20mentioned%20above%2C%20the%20income%20tax%20department%E2%80%99s%20letter%20to%20Oxfam%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.newslaundry.com%2F2023%2F10%2F14%2Fi-t-dept-revokes-tax-exemption-status-of-4-ngos-letters-to-two-mention-protests-against-adani%5C%22%3Esaid%3C%2Fa%3E%20the%20NGO%20was%20%E2%80%9Cinvolved%20in%20questioning%20the%20integrity%20of%20the%20government%20and%20discussing%20political%20issues%20in%20the%20meeting%2C%20which%20do%20not%20align%20with%20the%20objects%20of%20the%20assessee%E2%80%9D.%20It%20also%20alleged%20that%20the%20organisation%20was%20%E2%80%9Cworking%20for%20the%20benefit%20of%20a%20particular%20community%2C%E2%80%9D%20%3Cem%3ENewsLaundry%3C%2Fem%3E%20reported.%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EIn%20the%20letter%20to%20Environics%20Trust%2C%20the%20department%20said%20the%20organisation%20was%20%E2%80%9Cinvolved%20in%20Dhinkia%20protests%20against%20JSW%20Plants%E2%80%9D.%C2%A0%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EResidents%20of%20Dhinkia%20village%20in%20Odisha%20were%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Frights%2Fodisha-jindal-plant-20-houses-demolished-dhinkia%5C%22%3Eprotesting%20against%20the%20transfer%20of%20over%201%2C000%20hectares%20of%20land%20to%20Jindal%20Steel%20Works%3C%2Fa%3E%20for%20setting%20up%20a%2013.2%20million%20tonnes%20steel%20plant%20unit.%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EThey%20had%20alleged%20that%20the%20project%20and%20the%20corporate%20takeover%20of%20the%20land%20will%20lead%20to%20the%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Frights%2Fodisha-jindal-plant-20-houses-demolished-dhinkia%5C%22%3Edevastation%20of%20livelihoods%20of%20over%2040%2C000%20villagers%3C%2Fa%3E%20and%20will%20impact%20three%20villages%20of%20Dhinkia%2C%20Nuagaon%20and%20Gadakujang%20in%20the%20district.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3E%E2%80%98Raising%20questions%20against%20industries%20has%20become%20illegal%E2%80%99%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EOfficials%20at%20CARE%20India%20and%20LIFE%20chose%20not%20to%20comment%20on%20the%20revocation%20of%20their%20tax%20status.%20An%20official%20at%20the%20former%20told%20%3Cem%3ENewslaundry%3C%2Fem%3E%20that%20they%20did%20not%20want%20to%20divulge%20any%20specifics%20from%20the%20I-T%20department%E2%80%99s%20letter%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.newslaundry.com%2F2023%2F10%2F14%2Fi-t-dept-revokes-tax-exemption-status-of-4-ngos-letters-to-two-mention-protests-against-adani%5C%22%3Efearing%20backlash%3C%2Fa%3E.%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EWhile%20officials%20at%20LIFE%20said%20that%20they%20were%20%E2%80%9Ccurrently%20studying%20the%20options%20and%20have%20no%20specific%20comments%20to%20make%E2%80%9D%2C%20those%20at%20Environics%20said%20they%20were%20likely%20to%20challenge%20the%20Income%20Tax%20Order%20in%20the%20court%20coming%20week.%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3ERamamurthi%20Sreedhar%2C%20earth%20scientist%20and%20member%20of%20the%20core%20working%20team%20at%20the%20trust%20said%2C%20%E2%80%9CI%20think%20the%20order%20has%20nothing%20to%20do%20with%20our%20behaviour%20as%20an%20organisation.%20It%20is%20just%20that%20raising%20questions%20against%20the%20industries%20in%20India%20has%20become%20illegal%20now.%E2%80%9D%C2%A0%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EThe%20revocation%20of%20tax%20status%20has%20come%20amid%20an%20ongoing%20attack%20on%20NGOs%20across%20the%20country%20which%2C%20according%20to%20civil%20society%20members%20and%20political%20analysts%2C%20is%20an%20attempt%20to%20suppress%20organisations%20that%20are%20critical%20of%20the%20government.%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EIn%20September%202022%2C%20the%20I-T%20department%20had%20surveyed%20the%20offices%20of%20Oxfam%20India%2C%20Care%20India%2C%20Life%2C%20Environics%20Trust%2C%20CPR%20and%20Independent%20and%20Public%20Spirited%20Media%20Foundation%20(IPSMF)%2C%20%3Cem%3ENewsLaundry%3C%2Fem%3E%20reported.%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EA%20top%20official%20at%20CARE%20India%20told%20%3Cem%3ENewsLaundry%3C%2Fem%3E%2C%20%E2%80%9CThis%20raid%20was%20a%20part%20of%20a%20plot%20by%20the%20government.%20As%20part%20of%20a%20tax%20survey%20in%202022%2C%20they%20seized%20our%20computers%20and%20laptops%2C%20kept%20our%20staff%20locked%20in%20the%20Delhi%20office%20for%2072%20hours.%20Our%20staff%20was%20not%20allowed%20to%20go%20out.%20And%20not%20just%20Delhi%2C%20but%20our%20offices%20in%20Mumbai%20and%20Surat%20were%20also%20raided.%E2%80%9D%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EThe%20FCRA%20licences%20(under%20the%20Foreign%20Contribution%20Regulations%20Act)%20of%20Oxfam%2C%20LIFE%20and%20Environics%20Trust%20have%20already%20been%20cancelled.%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1697446251000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F10%2F16134849%2F36877237784_9786faab2d_c.jpg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Frights%2Ftax-exemption-status-of-4-more-ngos-revoked-i-t-dept-cites-protest-against-adani-as-reason-for-2%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22A%20top%20official%20at%20one%20of%20the%20NGOs%20told%20Newslaundry%2C%20'I%20think%20the%20order%20has%20nothing%20to%20do%20with%20our%20behaviour%20as%20an%20organisation.%20It%20is%20just%20that%20raising%20questions%20against%20the%20industries%20in%20India%20has%20become%20illegal%20now.'%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A82%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Frights%2Ftax-exemption-status-of-4-more-ngos-revoked-i-t-dept-cites-protest-against-adani-as-reason-for-2%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22Railways%20Unlikely%20to%20Meet%20Asset%20Monetisation%20Targets%20by%202024-25%3A%20Report%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%3Cimg%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F10%2F16130341%2F19351115534_6b836e91b8_c.jpg%5C%22%3E%3Cdiv%3E%20%3Cdiv%3E%20%3Cdiv%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3ENew%20Delhi%3A%3C%2Fstrong%3E%20The%20Indian%20Railways%20is%20unlikely%20to%20meet%20its%20asset%20monetisation%20targets%20for%20the%20four-year%20period%20ending%202024-2025%2C%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.deccanherald.com%2Fbusiness%2Findian-railways-unlikely-to-meet-rs-1-52-lcr-asset-monetisation-target-2727924%5C%22%3E%3Cem%3EDeccan%20Herald%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%20has%20reported.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3C%2Fdiv%3E%20%3C%2Fdiv%3E%20%3C%2Fdiv%3E%20%3Cp%3EThe%20NITI%20Aayog-developed%20%E2%80%98National%20Monetisation%20Pipeline%E2%80%99%2C%20brought%20in%202021-22%2C%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.india.gov.in%2Fspotlight%2Fnational-monetisation-pipeline-nmp%5C%22%3Eestimated%3C%2Fa%3E%20an%20aggregate%20asset%20monetisation%20potential%20of%20Rs%206%20lakh%20crores%20through%20core%20assets%20of%20the%20Union%20government%2C%20over%20a%20four-year%20period%2C%20from%20FY%202022%20to%20FY%202025.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EAmong%20the%20top%20five%20sectors%20in%20focus%20were%20the%20Railways%2C%20which%20aimed%20for%20the%20second%20largest%20target%20%E2%80%93%2025%25%20of%20the%20Rs%206%20lakh%20crore%20or%20Rs%201.52%20lakh%20crore.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EThe%20report%20quotes%20sources%20as%20having%20said%20that%20the%20current%20realisation%20remains%20%E2%80%9Cshort%20of%20aspiration%20at%20Rs%2020%2C000%20crore%20per%20year.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CFiguratively%2C%20it%20managed%20asset%20monetisation%20of%20around%20Rs%2030%2C000%20crore%20against%20the%20target%20of%20Rs%2057%2C222%20crore%20in%20FY23%2C%E2%80%9D%20the%20report%20says.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cdiv%3E%20%3Cdiv%3E%20%3Cdiv%3E%20%3Cp%3EThe%20report%20notes%20that%20the%20Railways%20had%20planned%20to%20redevelop%20400%20stations%2C%20privatise%20of%2090%20trains%20and%2015%20railway%20stadiums.%20In%20fact%2C%20development%20of%20stations%20is%20a%20significant%20part%20of%20monetisation%20plans%2C%20over%2050%25.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3C%2Fdiv%3E%20%3C%2Fdiv%3E%20%3Cp%3EThe%20report%20also%20has%20it%20that%20according%20to%20the%20NITI%20Aayog%2C%20the%20government%20has%20monetised%20assets%20worth%20Rs%2026%2C000%20crore%20during%20FY24%20against%20the%20target%20of%20Rs%201.6%20lakh%20crore%20for%20the%20current%20fiscal.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EFormer%20senior%20officials%20at%20the%20Railways%20told%20%3Cem%3EDH%3C%2Fem%3E%20that%20the%20sector%20has%20got%20a%20bit%20of%20a%20leeway%20from%20the%20government%20and%20that%20other%20sectors%20have%20done%20better.%20%3Cem%3EThe%20Wire%3C%2Fem%3E%20has%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fgovernment%2Frailways-telecom-petrol-asset-monetisation-targets-miss%5C%22%3Ereported%3C%2Fa%3E%20how%20the%20mining%20industry%20%E2%80%93%20which%20is%20one%20of%20the%20core%20industries%20of%20the%20economy%20%E2%80%93%20has%20been%20making%20up%20for%20the%20poor%20show%20of%20the%20Railways.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3C%2Fdiv%3E%20%3Cdiv%3E%20%3Cdiv%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%20%3C%2Fdiv%3E%20%3Cdiv%3E%20%3Cdiv%3E%20%3Cp%3EIn%20January%20this%20year%2C%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fgovernment%2Frailways-telecom-petrol-asset-monetisation-targets-miss%5C%22%3E%3Cem%3EFinancial%20Express%3C%2Fem%3E%20%3C%2Fa%3Ehad%20reported%20that%20the%20Railways%2C%20telecom%20and%20petroleum%20sectors%20are%20unlikely%20to%20meet%20their%20targets.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EIn%202021%2C%20in%20an%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Feconomy%2Finterview-p-chidambaram-national-monetisation-pipeline%5C%22%3E%20interview%20to%20%3Cem%3EThe%20Wire%3C%2Fem%3E%2C%3C%2Fa%3E%20former%20finance%20minister%20P.%20Chidambaram%20had%20noted%20that%20the%20NMP%20brought%20with%20itself%20concerns%20on%20corporate%20favouritism%2C%20rising%20costs%20for%20users%20and%20handing%20over%20strategic%20assets.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EMeanwhile%2C%20the%20Comptroller%20and%20Auditor%20General%20report%20on%20the%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcag.gov.in%2Fen%2Faudit-report%2Fdetails%2F119077%5C%22%3EUnion%20Government%2C%20(Railways)%20Railways%20Finances%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20presented%20to%20the%20parliament%20this%20monsoon%20session%20revealed%20that%20the%20Indian%20Railways%20could%20not%20generate%20a%20net%20surplus%20during%202021-22%20as%20compared%20to%202020-21.%20It%20also%20found%20that%20the%20Railways%20incurred%20an%20additional%20expenditure%20of%20Rs%207%2C778.43%20crore%20more%20than%20the%20sanctioned%20budget%20of%20Rs%205%2C7626.20.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3C%2Fdiv%3E%20%3C%2Fdiv%3E%20%3Cdiv%3E%20%3Cdiv%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%20%3C%2Fdiv%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1697444423000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F10%2F16130341%2F19351115534_6b836e91b8_c.jpg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fgovernment%2Fnmp-national-monetisation-pipeline-railways%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22'Deccan%20Herald'%20reports%20that%20the%20Railways%20has%20'been%20able%20to%20achieve%20only%20a%20lower%20single-digit%20percentage%20of%20its%20goal.'%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A6%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fgovernment%2Fnmp-national-monetisation-pipeline-railways%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22%E2%80%98In%20Standing%20With%20Palestine%2C%20We%20Are%20Also%20Standing%20Up%20For%20Ourselves%E2%80%99%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%3Cimg%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F10%2F16125107%2F20231014_125837-copy.jpg%5C%22%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EIn%20a%20recent%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fyoutu.be%2FZpzrIljG7hU%3Fsi%3DVQ_HlET2EnZkEonx%5C%22%3E%3Cspan%3EMasterclass%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cspan%3E%20on%20%E2%80%98Independent%20Thinking%20and%20Media%E2%80%99s%20Invisible%20Powers%E2%80%99%2C%20public%20intellectual%20Noam%20Chomsky%20recalls%20the%20day%20America%20dropped%20an%20atomic%20bomb%20on%20Hiroshima%3A%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cem%3E%3Cspan%3E%E2%80%9CAugust%206%2C%201945.%20I%20happened%20to%20be%20a%20counsellor%20at%20a%20summer%20camp%2C%20and%20the%20announcement%20came%20over%20the%20camp%20radio%20in%20the%20morning.%20An%20atom%20bomb%20had%20destroyed%20Hiroshima.%20Amazingly%20to%20me%2C%20everyone%20went%20on%20to%20their%20next%20activity%2C%20swimming%2C%20arts%20and%20crafts%2C%20whatever%20it%20was.%20I%20was%20just%20utterly%20appalled%2C%20almost%20beyond%20description.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EThere%20is%20indeed%20something%20bewildering%20about%20the%20apparent%20ease%20with%20which%20so%20many%20can%20ignore%20the%20tremendous%20suffering%20of%20their%20fellow%20humans%20in%20crisis%20and%20carry%20on%20enjoying%20themselves.%20A%20recent%20case%20in%20point%2C%20of%20course%2C%20is%20the%20Indo-Pak%20World%20Cup%20match%20in%20Ahmedabad%20on%20October%2014%20that%20millions%20in%20India%20watched%20and%20celebrated%20even%20as%20two%20million%20Palestinians%20in%20Gaza%20suffer%20what%20might%20well%20be%20called%20a%20second%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.un.org%2Funispal%2Fabout-the-nakba%2F%5C%22%3E%3Ci%3E%3Cspan%3Enakba%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fi%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cspan%3E.%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EOne%20can%E2%80%99t%20help%20but%20wonder%20if%20the%20noise%20of%20the%20celebratory%20firecrackers%20right%20after%20the%20Indian%20cricket%20team%E2%80%99s%20win%20reminded%20anyone%20in%20Narendra%20Modi%20stadium%20or%20those%20sitting%20in%20front%20of%20their%20TV%20screens%20%E2%80%93%20even%20faintly%20%E2%80%93%20of%20the%20Israeli%20bombs%20that%20have%20been%20exploding%20in%20Gaza%20for%20the%20last%20several%20days.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EOn%20the%20day%20of%20the%20much-awaited%20Indo-Pak%20match%2C%20however%2C%20about%20150%20citizens%20gathered%20at%20Jantar%20Mantar%20to%20protest%20Israeli%20atrocities%20in%20Palestine.%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EAt%20a%20time%20when%20empathy%20for%20one%E2%80%99s%20own%20countrymen%20and%20countrywomen%20seems%20to%20have%20dipped%20to%20an%20all-time%20low%2C%20it%20was%20heartening%20to%20see%20a%20group%20of%20people%2C%20however%20small%2C%20express%20solidarity%20for%20the%20suffering%20millions%20in%20another%20country.%20A%20genuine%20example%20of%20%E2%80%98%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ci%3E%3Cspan%3EVasudeva%20Kutumbakam%E2%80%99%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fi%3E%3Cspan%3E(The%20World%20Is%20One%20Family)%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Cspan%3E%2C%20words%20that%20our%20prime%20minister%20loves%20to%20bandy%20about%20on%20almost%20every%20international%20platform.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EHolding%20up%20a%20poster%20showing%20the%20progression%20of%20Israel%E2%80%99s%20occupation%20of%20Palestine%20from%201946%20to%202010%2C%20Maimoona%20Mollah%20from%20the%20All%20India%20Women%E2%80%99s%20Development%20Association%20(AIDWA)%20said%2C%20%E2%80%9CRight%20now%2C%20the%20Palestinians%20are%20being%20criticised%20as%20terrorists.%20If%20you%20take%20away%20people%E2%80%99s%20rights%2C%20even%20their%20right%20to%20live%20in%20their%20own%20homes%2C%20then%20they%20will%20retaliate.%20Israel%20did%20not%20take%20away%20the%20Palestinians%E2%80%99%20land%20by%20touching%20their%20feet%20and%20with%20love%2C%20did%20they%3F%20They%20have%20done%20it%20with%20brutal%20force%20all%20these%2075%20years.%20Yes%2C%20we%20condemn%20the%20retaliation%20and%20the%20killing%20of%20innocents%20in%20Israel%2C%20but%20innocents%20are%20being%20killed%20in%20Gaza%20too!%20And%20so%2C%20the%20killing%20has%20to%20be%20condemned%20on%20both%20sides!%20Having%20said%20that%2C%20the%20Palestinian%E2%80%99s%20struggle%20for%20self-determination%20and%20their%20homeland%20is%20very%20valid%20and%20just.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cdiv%20class%3D%5C%22wp-caption%5C%22%3E%3Cimg%20sizes%3D%5C%22(max-width%3A%20709px)%2085vw%2C%20(max-width%3A%20909px)%2067vw%2C%20(max-width%3A%201362px)%2062vw%2C%20840px%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F10%2F16125127%2F20231014_131959.jpg%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20width%3D%5C%221000%5C%22%20srcset%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F10%2F16125127%2F20231014_131959.jpg%201000w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F10%2F16125127%2F20231014_131959-300x169.jpg%20300w%5C%22%20class%3D%5C%22wp-image-680302%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22563%5C%22%3E%3Cp%20class%3D%5C%22wp-caption-text%5C%22%3EA%20woman%20holds%20up%20a%20poster%20showing%20the%20progression%20of%20Israel%E2%80%99s%20occupation%20of%20Palestine%20from%201946%20to%202010.%20Photo%3A%20Rohit%20Kumar%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EMollah%20reminded%20the%20gathering%3A%20%E2%80%9CIndia%20was%20once%20a%20very%20important%20member%20of%20the%20Non-Aligned%20Movement.%20We%20have%20always%20supported%20the%20cause%20of%20the%20Palestinians%2C%20so%20it%20is%20very%20worrying%20that%20in%20recent%20years%20we%20are%20no%20longer%20standing%20with%20the%20oppressed%20and%20the%20persecuted%20like%20we%20used%20to.%20Just%20as%20we%20stood%20with%20the%20oppressed%20in%20South%20Africa%20and%20spoke%20out%20against%20apartheid%2C%20we%20have%20also%20stood%20up%20against%20Zionist%20apartheid!%20But%20today%20it%20is%20very%20sad%20that%20we%20are%20kowtowing%20to%20American%20and%20Israeli%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ci%3E%3Cspan%3Edadagiri%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fi%3E%3Cspan%3E(bullying).%20Even%20if%20our%20political%20class%20is%20leaning%20away%20from%20the%20principles%20that%20have%20defined%20us%2C%20at%20least%20we%20the%20people%20of%20India%20should%20stand%20for%20Palestine%2C%20and%20for%20all%20people%20on%20this%20earth%20who%20are%20oppressed.%E2%80%9D%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3ENaveen%20Srivastava%2C%20an%20engineer%2C%20and%20political%20commentator%2C%20practically%20gave%20a%20small%20history%20class%20about%20the%20Palestine%20crisis%3A%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3E%E2%80%9CLet%20us%20not%20forget%20that%20the%20Israel-Palestine%20situation%20is%20primarily%20a%20battle%20between%20capitalism%20and%20socialism.%20This%20is%20not%20a%20religious%20war%20as%20the%20BJP%20government%20is%20trying%20to%20portray%20it!%20The%20Palestinians%E2%80%99%20land%20has%20been%20stolen%20from%20them%20over%20the%20decades%2C%20and%20today%20they%20are%20living%20in%2C%20as%20the%20international%20media%20calls%20it%2C%20an%20%E2%80%98open-air%20prison%E2%80%99.%20India%E2%80%99s%20support%20for%20Palestine%20began%20in%201931%20when%20Mahatma%20Gandhi%20first%20espoused%20the%20Palestine%20cause%20in%20a%20newspaper%20called%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ci%3E%3Cspan%3EThe%20Jewish%20Chronicle%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fi%3E%3Cspan%3E.%20He%20reiterated%20this%20again%20in%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ci%3E%3Cspan%3EHarijan%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fi%3E%3Cspan%3E%20magazine%20in%201938%20when%20he%20said%20that%20Palestine%20belongs%20to%20the%20Palestinians%20just%20as%20much%20as%20England%20belongs%20to%20the%20English.%20In%20fact%2C%20India%20didn%E2%80%99t%20even%20recognise%20the%20state%20of%20Israel%20when%20it%20was%20first%20established%20in%201948!%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3E%E2%80%9COur%20prime%20minister%20lauds%20the%20%E2%80%98nationalism%E2%80%99%20of%20Israel%2C%20but%20what%20about%20the%20nationalism%20of%20the%20Palestinians%20who%20have%20endured%20tremendous%20suffering%20for%20the%20last%20seven%20decades%3F%20The%20Palestinian%E2%80%99s%20struggle%20is%20our%20struggle%20too%20because%20the%20same%20types%20of%20fundamentalist%20forces%20are%20trying%20to%20divide%20our%20country%20on%20religious%20lines%20as%20well.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cdiv%20class%3D%5C%22wp-caption%5C%22%3E%3Cimg%20sizes%3D%5C%22(max-width%3A%20709px)%2085vw%2C%20(max-width%3A%20909px)%2067vw%2C%20(max-width%3A%201362px)%2062vw%2C%20840px%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F10%2F16125117%2F20231014_131946.jpg%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20width%3D%5C%221000%5C%22%20srcset%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F10%2F16125117%2F20231014_131946.jpg%201000w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F10%2F16125117%2F20231014_131946-300x169.jpg%20300w%5C%22%20class%3D%5C%22wp-image-680301%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22563%5C%22%3E%3Cp%20class%3D%5C%22wp-caption-text%5C%22%3EPhoto%3A%20Rohit%20Kumar%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3ESubash%20Chandran%2C%20a%20Supreme%20Court%20advocate%2C%20also%20pointed%20out%20how%20%E2%80%9Cthe%20ideology%20of%20the%20RSS%20is%20very%20similar%20to%20the%20ideology%20of%20the%20Zionists.%20They%20have%20been%20supporting%20Israel%20long%20befor